{"type":"message","id":"16cc164b","parentId":"fe37ae91","timestamp":"2026-02-23T23:00:00.193Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:10a19bb7-7afb-4b24-8478-62555b540c2d daily-ping-telegram] Execute the daily ping using existing infrastructure at /home/project/openclaw/:\n\n1. Run /home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh to fetch data with modified GitHub query for TRENDING repos (not just top stars)\n2. Run /home/project/openclaw/generate-daily-message.sh to create the formatted message\n3. Send the message via Telegram to 1087368827\n\nIMPORTANT MODIFICATIONS to make before running:\n- Update the GitHub API URL in daily-ping-cron.sh to fetch TRENDING instead of top stars:\n  OLD: https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5\n  NEW: https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=created:>2024-01-01&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=10\n- Update the message format in generate-daily-message.sh to match your preferred format with 📈📉 indicators\n- Format stars as K (e.g., 148K instead of 148045)\n\nIf the shell scripts fail, use Python directly via /home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-sender.py\n\nTimeout: 15 minutes (900 seconds)\nCurrent time: Tuesday, February 24th, 2026 — 7:00 AM (Asia/Singapore)"}],"timestamp":1771887600190}}
{"type":"message","id":"4db8dccb","parentId":"16cc164b","timestamp":"2026-02-23T23:07:51.671Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to execute the daily ping task. Let me break down what needs to be done:\n\n1. First, I need to read the existing scripts to understand their structure\n2. Make the modifications as requested:\n   - Update daily-ping-cron.sh to fetch TRENDING repos (created:>2024-01-01, sort by stars, 10 results)\n   - Update generate-daily-message.sh for the message format with 📈📉 indicators and K formatting\n3. Run the scripts\n4. Send the message via Telegram\n\nLet me start by reading","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" I'll execute the daily ping with the requested modifications. Let"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:0","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/project/openclaw/daily-ping-cron.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/project/openclaw/generate-daily-message.sh"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":8125,"output":200,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8325,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771887600192}}
{"type":"message","id":"e618a2da","parentId":"4db8dccb","timestamp":"2026-02-23T23:07:51.710Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Daily Ping Cron Job v2.0\n# Executes at 7:00 AM SGT (23:00 UTC)\n# Fixed: Better error handling, PATH setup for cron, explicit logging\n\n# Set PATH for cron environment\nexport PATH=\"/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n\n# Log file setup\nLOG_DIR=\"/home/project/openclaw/logs\"\nLOG_FILE=\"$LOG_DIR/daily-ping-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log\"\n\n# Ensure log directory exists\nif ! mkdir -p \"$LOG_DIR\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Cannot create log directory $LOG_DIR\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Check if we can write to log file\nif ! touch \"$LOG_FILE\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"ERROR: Cannot write to log file $LOG_FILE\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Function to log with timestamp\nlog() {\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z')] $1\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n}\n\nlog \"Starting daily ping job...\"\nlog \"Log file: $LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Fetch Bitcoin price from CoinGecko\nlog \"Fetching Bitcoin data from CoinGecko...\"\nBTC_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true\" 2>&1)\nCURL_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: Bitcoin fetch failed (curl exit: $CURL_EXIT)\"\n    log \"Curl output: $BTC_DATA\"\nelse\n    BTC_PRICE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd\":[0-9]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n    BTC_CHANGE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd_24h_change\":[-0-9.]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n    \n    if [ -z \"$BTC_PRICE\" ]; then\n        log \"ERROR: Could not parse Bitcoin price from response\"\n        log \"Response: $BTC_DATA\"\n    else\n        log \"Bitcoin: $BTC_PRICE (change: $BTC_CHANGE%)\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Fetch top GitHub repos\nlog \"Fetching GitHub data...\"\nGH_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=created:>2024-01-01&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=10\" 2>&1)\nCURL_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: GitHub fetch failed (curl exit: $CURL_EXIT)\"\nelse\n    # Verify we got valid JSON\n    if echo \"$GH_DATA\" | grep -q '\"total_count\":'; then\n        log \"GitHub data fetched successfully\"\n    else\n        log \"ERROR: GitHub response invalid\"\n        log \"Response preview: $(echo \"$GH_DATA\" | head -c 200)\"\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Fetch stock data using uv run (more reliable than source activate)\nlog \"Fetching stock data (NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD)...\"\n\n# Use uv run from the correct directory\ncd /home/project/openclaw || exit 1\n\nSTOCK_OUTPUT=$(uv run python3 << 'PYTHON_SCRIPT'\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\nimport sys\n\ntickers = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresults = {}\n\ntry:\n    for symbol in tickers:\n        try:\n            t = yf.Ticker(symbol)\n            info = t.info\n            current_price = info.get('currentPrice') or info.get('regularMarketPrice', 0)\n            prev_close = info.get('previousClose', 0)\n            change_pct = info.get('regularMarketChangePercent')\n            if change_pct is None and prev_close > 0:\n                change_pct = ((current_price - prev_close) / prev_close) * 100\n            results[symbol] = {\n                'price': current_price,\n                'change_pct': change_pct or 0,\n                'company': info.get('shortName', symbol)\n            }\n        except Exception as e:\n            results[symbol] = {'error': str(e)}\n    \n    print(json.dumps(results))\n    sys.exit(0)\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(json.dumps({'error': str(e)}))\n    sys.exit(1)\nPYTHON_SCRIPT\n2>&1)\n\nPYTHON_EXIT=$?\n\nif [ $PYTHON_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    log \"ERROR: Stock data fetch failed (python exit: $PYTHON_EXIT)\"\n    log \"Python output: $STOCK_OUTPUT\"\nelse\n    echo \"$STOCK_OUTPUT\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n    log \"Stock data fetched successfully\"\nfi\n\nlog \"Daily ping job completed\"\n\n# Return appropriate exit code\nif [ $CURL_EXIT -ne 0 ] || [ $PYTHON_EXIT -ne 0 ]; then\n    exit 1\nelse\n    exit 0\nfi\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771888071708}}
{"type":"message","id":"e488b4ef","parentId":"e618a2da","timestamp":"2026-02-23T23:07:51.734Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Generate Daily Ping Message File\n# This script reads the log and creates a formatted message file\n\nLOG_FILE=\"/home/project/openclaw/logs/daily-ping-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log\"\nMESSAGE_FILE=\"/home/project/openclaw/daily-message.txt\"\n\n# Check if log exists\nif [ ! -f \"$LOG_FILE\" ]; then\n    echo \"Error: Log file not found\" >&2\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# Extract Bitcoin data from log\nBTC_PRICE=$(grep -o '\"usd\":[0-9]*' \"$LOG_FILE\" | tail -1 | cut -d: -f2)\nBTC_CHANGE=$(grep -o '\"usd_24h_change\":[-0-9.]*' \"$LOG_FILE\" | tail -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n\n# Format change with trend indicator\nif (( $(echo \"$BTC_CHANGE > 0\" | bc -l 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\") )); then\n    BTC_TREND=\"📈\"\nelse\n    BTC_TREND=\"📉\"\nfi\n\n# Get stock data JSON from log and format\nSTOCK_SECTION=\"\"\nif grep -q '\"NVDA\"' \"$LOG_FILE\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    STOCK_SECTION=\"📊 Tech Stocks\\n\"\n    for symbol in NVDA MSFT GOOGL INTC META AMD; do\n        PRICE=$(grep -oP \"\\\"$symbol\\\":.*?\\\"price\\\":\\s*[0-9.]+\" \"$LOG_FILE\" | grep -o '[0-9.]*$' | head -1)\n        CHANGE=$(grep -oP \"\\\"$symbol\\\":.*?\\\"change_pct\\\":\\s*[-0-9.]+\" \"$LOG_FILE\" | grep -o '[-0-9.]*$' | head -1)\n        if [ -n \"$PRICE\" ] && [ -n \"$CHANGE\" ]; then\n            if (( $(echo \"$CHANGE >= 0\" | bc -l 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\") )); then\n                TREND=\"📈\"\n            else\n                TREND=\"📉\"\n            fi\n            # Format change with + sign if positive\n            if (( $(echo \"$CHANGE >= 0\" | bc -l 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\") )); then\n                CHANGE_FMT=\"+$(printf \"%.2f\" $CHANGE)%%\"\n            else\n                CHANGE_FMT=\"$(printf \"%.2f\" $CHANGE)%%\"\n            fi\n            STOCK_SECTION+=\"\\n• $symbol: \\$$PRICE ($CHANGE_FMT) $TREND\"\n        fi\n    done\nfi\n\n# Get GitHub trending repos from log\nGITHUB_SECTION=\"\"\nif grep -q '\"total_count\":' \"$LOG_FILE\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    GITHUB_SECTION=\"\\n\\n🚀 Trending GitHub Repos\\n\"\n    # Extract repo names and stars from the log - careful with the pattern\n    REPO_DATA=$(grep -o '\"full_name\":\"[^\"]*\"' \"$LOG_FILE\" | head -10)\n    STAR_DATA=$(grep -o '\"stargazers_count\":[0-9]*' \"$LOG_FILE\" | head -10)\n    \n    # Combine using paste\n    if [ -n \"$REPO_DATA\" ] && [ -n \"$STAR_DATA\" ]; then\n        i=1\n        while IFS= read -r repo_line && IFS= read -r star_line <&3; do\n            repo=$(echo \"$repo_line\" | sed 's/\"full_name\":\"//g; s/\"$//g')\n            stars=$(echo \"$star_line\" | sed 's/\"stargazers_count\"://g')\n            \n            # Format stars as K if >= 1000\n            if [ \"$stars\" -ge 1000 ] 2>/dev/null; then\n                stars_fmt=\"$(echo \"scale=1; $stars/1000\" | bc 2>/dev/null || echo \"$((stars/1000))\")K\"\n            else\n                stars_fmt=\"$stars\"\n            fi\n            \n            GITHUB_SECTION+=\"\\n$i. $repo ⭐ $stars_fmt\"\n            i=$((i+1))\n        done < <(echo \"$REPO_DATA\") 3< <(echo \"$STAR_DATA\")\n    fi\nfi\n\n# Create message\ncat > \"$MESSAGE_FILE\" << EOF\n📅 Daily Ping — $(date +\"%A, %B %d, %Y\")\n\n💰 Bitcoin\n• Price: \\$${BTC_PRICE:-N/A} USD\n• 24h: ${BTC_CHANGE:-N/A}% $BTC_TREND\n\n${STOCK_SECTION}${GITHUB_SECTION}\n\n—\n⏰ $(date +\"%H:%M %Z\")\nEOF\n\necho \"Message generated: $MESSAGE_FILE\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771888071732}}
